### Test 1: Create a session with multiple players
POST http://localhost:3000/api/sessions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "1",
  "gameId": "1",
  "players": [
    { "name": "Alice", "isWinner": true },
    { "name": "Bob", "isWinner": false },
    { "name": "Charlie", "isWinner": false }
  ],
  "date": "2026-04-09T19:00:00.000Z"
}

### Test 2: Create another session for the same game
POST http://localhost:3000/api/sessions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "1",
  "gameId": "1",
  "players": [
    { "name": "Alice", "isWinner": false },
    { "name": "Bob", "isWinner": true }
  ],
  "date": "2026-04-08T20:30:00.000Z"
}

### Test 3: Get all sessions for user
GET http://localhost:3000/api/sessions?userId=1
Accept: application/json

### Test 4: Get sessions filtered by game
GET http://localhost:3000/api/sessions?userId=1&gameId=1
Accept: application/json

### Test 5: Create session without isWinner (defaults to false)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/sessions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "1",
  "gameId": "1",
  "players": [
    { "name": "David" },
    { "name": "Eve" }
  ]
}

### Test 6: Missing players field (should fail with 400)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/sessions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "1",
  "gameId": "1"
}

### Test 7: Empty players array (should fail with 400)
POST http://localhost:3000/api/sessions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "1",
  "gameId": "1",
  "players": []
}
